    "updated_at": "2014-12-10T11:17:00Z",
    "body": "I'm not sure whether `~` in PATH is legal or not. In my unscientific test, `bash` expands `~` in PATH. However, is this behavior specified in POSIX? I've always included only full paths in PATH, so I'm asking here just to be sure.\n\nAnd what should be done in Windows? I'm also not sure there is the concept of `~` in Windows, though `%HOME%` exists.\n",
